### Checklist

- [x] This is a bug report.
- [ ] This is a feature request.
- [ ] This is a plugin (improvement) request.
- [x] I have read the contribution guidelines.

### Description
The streams all seem to freeze after about 5 seconds then and after a further 15-20 seconds the stream closes.
This issue started happening today.  tested on 0.6.0 and 0.10.0
Checked this on multiple Ustream channels..  NASA's HDEV and leolaporte (Twit.tv)
This is happening on my raspberry pi's and I've also tested by running this on a cloud server I have with ubuntu (I just output the stream to a file rather than playing it of course)... the recorded file has the same issues I see with the player version and the debug output appears to be the same.  I did that cloud server test just to hopefully rule out a local ISP / routing issue.  

Could Ustream have made some funky API change?    

Thanks for checking this out.  
...

### Expected / Actual behavior
Well.. it shouldn't do that.  :-)
...

### Reproduction steps / Explicit stream URLs to test
First two command lines are on a Raspberry pi (hence use of omxplayer).  I also switched to lower quality streams just in case it was a bandwidth issue (which with my 400Mbs internet pipe should not be a factor anyway)
1. streamlink -l debug http://www.ustream.tv/channel/iss-hdev-payload best --player omxplayer --fifo
2. streamlink -l debug http://www.ustream.tv/leolaporte best --player omxplayer --fifo
